description.p:
Examples of the above-mentioned diluent are aliphatic
hydrocarbone such as pentane, hexane, heptane and octane;
aromatic hydrocarbons such as benzene, toluene and xylene;
alicyclic hydrocarbons such as cyclohexane and cyclopentane;
and halogenated hydrocarbons such as 1,2-dichloroethane and
monochlorobenzene.
